UserComments.Comment:
Plugged in to the 3 pin socket with my own cable, flicked the switch on and charged no problems.
I did phone union square car park before hand in the morning and they put a cone in front of a space for me. At lunch time when we arrived 4 ICE were parked in EV spaces. So, even though there were other spaces, I suggest reserving a space beforehand, just in case. It doesn't cost anything to reserve a space.

All official sockets currently broken, but there is one space a little beyond these bays, just before the parent and child bays, that has access to a socket behind some pipes. Site owners have been happy to let me use this.

CommentType.Title: Fault Report (Notice To Users And Operator)

UserComments.Comment: All 8 sockets (for the 10 bays) currently broken due to being hit by bumpers of cars parking in these bays.
Very poorly signposted so guaranteed to be ICEd when at all busy. Sockets at bumper height with no protection so frequently damaged.
These sockets seems to share the same circuit, so if more than one car plugs in then the last one gets the charge and the others get cut off!

MediaItems.Comment: Ice ice baby! All but one occupied by non electric cars! And only 3mph - could try harder:)
10 spaces all iced! And 3mph charge rate nice!

Reported to be offline with no ETA on a fix
Phoned ahead, very polite staff, they  made sure a  bay was available for us. Filled us full of free coffee and biccies
Is the charger truly public, as stated, or reserved for Nissan vehicles?

The DC fast charger failed on my next visit to AF Noble. I'd phoned ahead to check it was working a few days before but arriving first thing in the morning seems unpopular with it. I'd regard it's reliability as slightly marginal at present, I only have a 1/3 success rate with it. The next nearest 10A/16A charging point is in Dynamic Earth in Edinburgh, and it's an easy place to pass a few hours of slow charging!

I went up to A F Noble to meet @iangarethreeves who drove to Edinburgh from Glasgow in his Nissan LEAF. He called me when he got to the dealership and I reached him 20 minutes later. His LEAF was charging on the CHAdeMO DC. After just a few minutes of getting a coffee and starting to chat the dealer (Jim, a truly nice guy) came over to say that the charge was at 87%. A few more minutes and it was done. 

First time I've witnessed DC fast charge - very impressive. It truly extends the range of an EV in a very practical way.
